le, yes, but as your skill goes up, that's no longer accurate, and intelligence affects it too.  Maybe &quot;Base fizzle percentage&quot; if you prefer it in percent.<br><br>From EqCaster:<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &gt;<br>&gt; Summon Warder<br>&gt; ...<br>&gt; Spell Duration: Unknown<br>&gt; Duration Formula: 3600</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>I notice a lot of the &quot;Unknown duration formula&quot; values appear to be the actual durations.  The beastlord warder pet was recently confirmed by Absor to last up to 10 hours (see <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000495.html">this post</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->), and its duration formula is 3600, so 3600 units = 10 hours, 360 units = an hour, 6 units = a minute, 1 unit = 10 seconds.  I see similar values on wizard familiar spells, which also seem to last up to 10 hours.<br><br>Also from EqCaster:<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &gt;<br>&gt; Familiar<br>&gt; ...<br>&gt; Modifies Casting Skill (4)?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>That attribute is the same attribute that is documented as increasing &quot;effective casting level&quot; for Intellectual Superiority.  It's likely used for resistance checks.  So with my Familiar up, my resists are checked as if I were level 58 +4 = 62.  It probably also affects fizzle checks, since there's a dragon spell in there somewhere which I'm told makes you fizzle like mad with a large negative value in that attribute.<br><br>EDIT: Forgot one:<br><br>From EqCaster:<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &gt;<br>&gt; Glimpse<br>&gt; ...<br>&gt; Increase Magnification by 55% (L4)<br><br>&gt; Gaze<br>&gt; ...<br>&gt; Increase Magnification by 50% (L12)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>Notice the percentage decreases as the zoom increases.  I think this should be reported as &quot;Zoom in on middle NN% of the screen.&quot;  Either that or report it as &quot;Increase magnification by (10000/v)%&quot;, so that Glimpse would report 10000/50 = 200% magnification.<br><br>---<br><br>Thanks once again for such an enormously useful program.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br> <p><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tr>  <td style=filter:glow(color=#303870 strength=1)>   <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73405" style=text-decoration:none target=new><font size=2 color=#6070E0>Baron&nbsp;Twiddle&nbsp;O`Toole</font></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bruneofwar35127" style=text-decoration:none target=new><font size=2 color=#6070E0>&lt;Rune&nbsp;of&nbsp;War&gt;</font></a>  </td>  <td valign=bottom width=100%>   <font size=1 color=#CCCCCC>    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>58.42 <strike>Evoker</strike> Cabbie / Veeshan</i>   </font>  </td> </tr> <tr>  <td colspan=2>   <font size=1 color=#CCCCCC>    <font color=#F00000>Twiddle scowls at you, ready to attack -- what would you like his tombstone to say?</font>   </font>  </td> </tr></table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utwiddleotoole.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiddle OToole</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_bullet.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/21/02 11:15:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvaslin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaslin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/21/02 11:31:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13160.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EqCaster - New Site - Need Wizard input!</span><hr size=1> Wow!  I've certainly stumbled i